INSTALLATION
    GNU BPEL2oWFN can be easily compiled and installed. See file "INSTALL"
    for instructions.

    GNU BPEL2oWFN uses a lot of generated code. If you want to make changes
    to the source code, you might need the following tools to regenerate
    the code:
     * Flex (http://flex.sourceforge.net)
     * Bison (http://www.gnu.org/software/bison)
     * Kimwitu++ (http://www.nongnu.org/kimwitu-pp)
     * Gengetopt (http://www.gnu.org/software/gengetopt)


DOCUMENTATION
    The directory "doc" contains a documentation of GNU BPEL2oWFN. It can
    also be downloaded at
    <http://service-technology.org/files/bpel2owfn/bpel2owfn.pdf>.
    Furthermore, the directory "doc" contains a technical report
    ("semantics.pdf") describing the Petri net translation implemented by
    GNU BPEL2oWFN.
